WRITING.TITLE: [NSV] 3 weeks of working out and eating better - I've lost a fat roll on my back!
WRITING.TEXT:
I started my journey early January and I've been hitting the gym 2-3 times a week, and logging everything into MyFitnessPal. I've been a tiny bit discouraged in that the scale hasn't gone down has much as I hoped. People have told me not to worry about that, as I've mainly been lifting, and not doing cardio as much.
Anyway, today, I had a shower to get ready for work and my partner was so surprised and said my back looked different. I got her to take a picture to compare, sure enough, one roll is gone! I can't believe it, after 3 weeks!
Maybe NSFW because I'm in my undieroos. Here is before and after: https://imgur.com/a/lONGo
Absolutely amazing. You look totally fantastic! Keep up the hard work :)

This. My PT is the best money I've spent. She's very motivating, teaches me correct technique, checks how I'm feeling the next days after a hard workout, reviews my food (I send her myfitness pal weekly reports), comes and says hello to me at the gym when I'm working out on my own, and for me personally, the best thing is that I don't want to let her down. Every time I go to eat something bad, I think "hmm, I'll have to put that into MFP, and she's going to see it". So I don't eat it. Overall, she keeps me motivated and i look forward to my sessions.
